Thorax
. Prothorax. Anterior pronotal lobe largely yellowish; middle and posterior pronotal lobe yellowish with a large oval pale yellow marking dorsally on the middle pronotal lobe (
Fig. 6e
); posterior pronotal lobe well developed, posterior margin slightly curved upward in lateral view (

Fig. 
6g

), slightly produced to rear at corners in dorsal view (
Fig. 6h
). Propleuron entirely black. Synthorax (
Fig. 6e
). Mesepisternum black with long yellowish antehumeral stripes, broad at base, narrower posteriorly; mesepimeron entirely black. Metepisternum black with a yellowish stripe, covering the spiracle and connected to metakatepisternum. Metepimeron black with a blue mark in the upper corner near the wing bases, lower half yellow. 
Legs
(
Fig. 6e
). Coxa and trochanter entirely yellow; femur yellow, flexor and extensor surfaces brownish; tibia black; tarsus and claws dark yellow. 
Wings
hyaline, 16–17 Px in both wings. Pterostigma dark reddish, covering one underlying cell (
Fig. 7h
).
